## Git Branch Naming

### Branch Naming Convention

Use descriptive branch names with prefixes:

- **Feature**: `feat/feature-name` (e.g., `feat/user-profile`)
- **Fix**: `fix/bug-description` (e.g., `fix/login-error`)
- **Refactor**: `refactor/component-name` (e.g., `refactor/auth-flow`)
- **Chore**: `chore/task-description` (e.g., `chore/update-deps`)
- **Docs**: `docs/documentation-name` (e.g., `docs/api-reference`)

### Commit Messages

Follow Conventional Commits format (see `gen-commit-message.md`):

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

- <brief change 1>
- <brief change 2>
```

**Types**: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `style`, `chore`, `docs`, `perf`, `test`

