## Code Organization

### File Structure

**Organize files in this order:**

1. Imports (grouped and sorted)
2. Type/Interface definitions
3. Constants
4. Helper functions
5. Main component/function
6. Exports

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Well-organized file structure
// 1. Imports
import { useState } from 'react';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';

// 2. Types
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
}

// 3. Constants
const MAX_ITEMS = 10;

// 4. Helpers
function formatTitle(title: string): string {
  return title.toUpperCase();
}

// 5. Main component
export function Component({ title }: ComponentProps) {
  return <div>{formatTitle(title)}</div>;
}
```

### Function Organization

**Within a file, organize functions:**

1. Pure utility functions first
2. Helper functions
3. Main exported functions last

---

## Export Conventions

### Named Exports (Preferred)

**Use named exports for components and utilities:**

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Named export
export function UserProfile() {
  return <div>Profile</div>;
}

export function getUserData() {
  // ...
}

// ❌ BAD: Default export (unless required by framework)
export default function UserProfile() {
  return <div>Profile</div>;
}
```

### Barrel Exports

**Use index files for clean imports:**

```typescript
// packages/db — schema tables are exported from `@app/db/schema`
import { projects, users } from '@app/db/schema';
```

